{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionEvent-Based Vision Sensor (EVS) detects luminance changes asynchronously and will output event data immediately, which has the advantages of low power consumption and high sensitivity, and is suitable for capturing high dynamic range visual information without blurring.",
    "However, the inability to capture color information greatly limits the application scope of event cameras.",
    "Hybrid Eventbased Vision Sensor (HybridEVS) [11] is a novel hybrid * Co-first authors, † corresponding author.",
    "sensor formed by combining traditional frame-based sensor and event-based sensor.",
    "It combines the advantages of these sensors, offering high temporal resolution, low latency, and exceptional dynamic range while still capturing color information with higher Signal-to-Noise Ratio (SNR)."
  ]
}